OL,3,CSheffield gets biggest emergency rough
OL,4,Csleeping grant outside London
OL,6,FThe latest official statistics show
OL,7,Fmore than 358,000 households contacted
OL,8,Ftheir local authority for support
OL,9,Fafter being threatened with
OL,10,Fhomelessness or losing their home in
OL,11,F2023-24, up more than 10% in a year.
OL,13,FThe number of rough sleepers who died
OL,14,Fon the streets increased by 42% in
OL,15,F2023.
OL,17,FHomeless people are up to 12 times
OL,18,Fmore likely than the general
OL,19,Fpopulation to die prematurely.
